{"source_key":"sha256-ed3e9d225205f4174c541a978114be37","record_index":336,"record_hash":"sha256:22c014812170656c2f2a138bddaedd937312645d97094585a4f93b10f53b8794","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:05:11.729Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: cafbb5\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1936\nOutput:\nthe relevant tool call or assistant claim, then return to the overview without\nlosing context.\n\nRaw transcript records should remain available, but they should be treated as an\nevidence drawer, not the primary browsing mode.\n\n## Ranking And Highlighting\n\nThe page should rank or highlight likely relevant turns. Relevance is a product\ndecision above `but-agentlog`.\n\nGood signals:\n\n- direct review target observation\n- direct branch target observation\n- capture time near commits or PR updates\n- prompts mentioning the feature, bug, branch, or files\n- assistant claims about implementation or tests\n- tool calls that run tests, builds, formatters, or linters\n- later path or commit evidence, if added\n\nWeak signals:\n\n- backfilled turns with only capture-time environment snapshots\n- broad sessions that span unrelated work\n- sidecar review sessions that discuss the branch but did not implement it\n- turns related only through current branch state\n\nThe UI should expose why a turn is highlighted. Reviewers should not have to\nguess why a session appears.\n\n## Privacy And Publication\n\nAgent Trail is more sensitive than local handoff because it is meant to be\nopened by colleagues.\n\nFor public v1, Agent Trail treats a publicly fetchable `refs/meta/main` as\nalready published metadata. On-demand URL replacement does not grant access to\nprivate data; it only renders a review page from metadata that is fetchable\nwithout credentials.\n\nThere is no Forge-specific public redaction pass in v1. That makes\n`but-agentlog`'s public/read projection load-bearing. Forge must only render\nrecords returned by that projection; it must not read or render raw internal\nrecords directly.\n\nThe rendered data must preserve these `but-agentlog` guarantees:\n\n- records must be redacted\n- local filesystem paths should not be exposed\n- raw provider session ids should not be exposed\n- hidden/system/developer prompts should not be exposed\n- source records \n[TRUNCATED]\nes both review and branch targets\n- refresh and invalidation behavior for cached snapshots\n- detailed UI layout beyond the MVP page contract\n- generated summaries\n- private repository access\n- GitHub OAuth and GitButler workspace auth\n- configurable metadata remotes and arbitrary metadata locations\n- GitHub check-run, app panel, PR description, or bot-comment integration\n- user-controlled session hiding/exclusion before publishing\n- reviewer follow-up questions against the trail\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe first implementation should satisfy:\n\n- route parses `/<owner>/<repo>/pull/<number>` for the Agent Trail domain\n- server verifies the GitHub repository and PR are publicly readable\n- fork PRs return a clear unsupported state\n- first request initializes a bare/cache repository; later requests re-fetch\n- server fetches only `refs/meta/main` for metadata in v1\n- snapshot generation is pinned to the fetched metadata OID\n- lookup searches the PR review target and PR head branch\n- results dedupe sessions/turns and rank review matches above branch-only matches\n- page shows PR identity, snapshot metadata/OID, sessions, match reasons, turn\n  timeline, and expandable evidence\n- branch-only matches are labeled weaker than review matches\n- raw records are available only through bounded drill-down\n- Forge renders only `but-agentlog` redacted public/read projection data\n- tests cover URL parsing, target normalization, review+branch merge/ranking,\n  missing metadata, no matching sessions, and fork PR rejection\n\n## Implementation Boundary\n\nKeep the primitive crate boring.\n\n`but-agentlog` owns:\n\n- capture\n- redaction\n- GitMeta storage\n- related-session lookup\n- compact skim/read primitives\n- bounded exact record reads\n\nAgent Trail owns:\n\n- PR/review entry point\n- URL and publishing flow\n- permission model\n- review-specific ranking\n- page layout and copy\n- share-specific projection\n- optional generated summaries\n\nIf Agent Trail needs code in this repository, prefer a separate module or crate\nlayered above `but-agentlog`.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:05:11.729Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}